# Testing

## Test categories (one folder each)

| Folder              | Marker          | Purpose                                  |
|---------------------|-----------------|------------------------------------------|
| `tests/`            | (none / unit)   | Unit tests on individual modules         |
| `tests/strategy/`   | (none)          | Strategy-level behavior on synthetic data |
| `tests/e2e/`        | `e2e`           | API + backtest end-to-end                |
| `tests/security/`   | `security`      | Invariants (LLM isolation, no secrets)   |
| `ai_evals/deepeval/`| (none)          | LLM contract tests (offline by default)  |

Run a category alone with `pytest -q -m e2e` or `pytest -q tests/strategy`.

## Required

- Every public function in `data/`, `risk/`, `strategies/`, `backtests/`
  has at least one unit test covering accept and reject paths.
- A new strategy ships with a test in `tests/strategy/test_<name>.py`
  asserting target_positions on a synthetic OHLCV fixture.
- A new API endpoint ships with an e2e test in `tests/e2e/test_api_app.py`.
- A new prompt ships with both a deepeval test and a promptfoo case.

## Forbidden

- `pytest.skip(...)` without a linked GitHub issue and a clear unblock condition.
- Tests that hit the network. Use fixtures or `httpx.MockTransport`.
- Tests that depend on file ordering or process-global state.
- Mocking `risk.engine.RiskEngine` in a way that bypasses checks. Mock the
  *broker*, not the risk engine.

## Backtest determinism test

A canonical fixture in `tests/test_backtest_determinism.py` re-runs the
same config and asserts byte-identical `metrics.json`. Adding stochasticity
without a seed breaks this test.
